ad and nuanced political theories central to Black life. In doing so, African American Political Thought: A Collected History transforms how we understand the past and future of political thinking in the West.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aAfrican American philosophers. 0aAfrican American philosophy. 0aAfrican American political activists. 0aAfrican AmericansxPolitics and governmentxPhilosophy. 0aAmerican literaturexAfrican American authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aBlack nationalism. 0aPolitical sciencezUnited StatesxPhilosophy. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aangela, davis, books, black, women, history, capitalism, liberation, revolution, critical race theory, marxism, alice walker, web dubois, racism, united states, frederick douglass, nationalism, bookert washington, ida b wells, marcus garvey, langston huges, clarence thomas, power.1 aAllen, Danielle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBalfour, Lawrie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBogues, Anthony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBromell, Nick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarretta, Vincent, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChappell, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDawson, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDrabinski, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFerguson, Jeffrey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrank, Jason, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGriffin, Farah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJagmohan, Desmond, econtributo